ABUJA – The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has approved the update of the party’s timetable and schedule of activities for the 2023 general elections. Consequently, the party has approved May 23, 2022 for governorship Primaries, May 21, 2022 for Senatorial District Primaries and May 20, for House of Representatives. Others are; May 18, for the State House of Assembly (State Constituency Congress) and May 10, for Local Government Area (LGA) Congress to elect one National Delegate per LGA and one Person living with disability in the 774 Local Government Areas. -Advertisement- According to the party, in a statement by its spokesman, Hon. Debo Ologunagba, “all aspirants to various positions, critical stakeholders, members of our Party across the country as well as relevant agencies of government should please take note.”